name: Brendan Carr
summary: President Trump has announced his intention to appoint Brendan Carr as Chairman of the Federal Communications Commission (FCC). This news has been widely reported by several media outlets, including CNN, The New York Times, NPR, The Wall Street Journal, The Washington Post, POLITICO, NBC News, Axios, CBS News, and Al Jazeera English. Carr is currently an FCC Commissioner and has been a vocal advocate for challenging the dominance of big technology companies. In a document titled "Project 2025," Carr outlined his vision for the FCC, which includes promoting competition in the telecom industry and curbing the power of large tech companies. His appointment is expected to have significant implications for the regulation of technology and telecommunications in the United States.

name: Daikin
summary: The iconic home of the Houston Astros, formerly known as Minute Maid Park, will be renamed Daikin Park on January 1, 2025. The new 15-year naming rights deal with the Japanese air conditioning manufacturer, Daikin, marks a departure from the 19-year partnership with Minute Maid. This move reflects the growing trend of naming rights deals in sports stadiums, as companies seek to align their brands with popular teams and venues. Daikin's prominence in the air conditioning industry aligns with the park's commitment to fan comfort and sustainability. The naming change, effective next year, will mark a new era for the beloved Astros' home field.
